# Inline Styling Examples in Zolt

## Basic Inline Styling

Using `||text||{attr}` to style text spans:
- This is ||important text||{color=red} within a sentence.
- This is ||highlighted content||{background=yellow}.
- This is ||bold and blue||{font-weight=bold color=blue}.

## Multiple Styles

Combining multiple attributes:
- ||Warning: This is critical||{color=red font-weight=bold background=yellow}
- ||Success message||{color=green font-weight=bold}
- ||Info text||{color=blue background=light-blue}

## Text Sizing

Different text sizes:
- ||Small text||{font-size=0.8em}
- ||Normal text||{font-size=1em}
- ||Large text||{font-size=1.5em}
- ||Extra large text||{font-size=2em}

## Font Styling

Font variations:
- ||Bold text||{font-weight=bold}
- ||Italic text||{font-style=italic}
- ||Underlined text||{text-decoration=underline}
- ||Strikethrough text||{text-decoration=line-through}

## Colors

Color examples:
- ||Red text||{color=red}
- ||Blue text||{color=blue}
- ||Green text||{color=green}
- ||Custom purple||{color=#8B5CF6}
- ||RGB color||{color=rgb(139, 92, 246)}

## Backgrounds

Background styling:
- ||Yellow highlight||{background=yellow}
- ||Light gray background||{background=#F3F4F6}
- ||Custom background||{background=#FEF3C7 color=#92400E}

## Borders

Adding borders:
- ||Bordered text||{border=1px solid black}
- ||Dashed border||{border=2px dashed blue}
- ||Rounded corners||{border=1px solid red border-radius=4px}

## Text Alignment

Alignment within inline spans (works in block contexts):

||Left aligned||{text-align=left display=block}

||Center aligned||{text-align=center display=block}

||Right aligned||{text-align=right display=block}

## Combined Examples

### Emphasis and Color

The ||quick brown fox||{color=brown font-weight=bold} jumps over the ||lazy dog||{color=gray font-style=italic}.

### Code References

Use the ||print()||{font-family=monospace background=#F3F4F6 padding=2px 6px} function to output text.

The ||status||{font-family=monospace background=black color=lime padding=2px 6px} command shows system status.

### Labels and Badges

- ||NEW||{background=blue color=white padding=2px 8px border-radius=12px font-size=0.8em}
- ||IMPORTANT||{background=red color=white padding=2px 8px border-radius=12px font-weight=bold}
- ||Beta||{background=purple color=white padding=2px 8px border-radius=4px font-size=0.75em}

### Inline Code Blocks

- ||def hello():||{font-family=monospace background=#1F2937 color=#10B981 padding=2px 6px}
- ||    print("Hello, World!")||{font-family=monospace background=#1F2937 color=#F3F4F6}

### Text Highlights

In this paragraph, ||certain words||{background=yellow} are highlighted to draw ||attention||{background=yellow font-weight=bold} to them.

## Practical Use Cases

### Documentation

The ||--verbose||{font-family=monospace color=purple} flag enables detailed output.

### Technical Writing

The ||CPU||{font-weight=bold} (||Central Processing Unit||{font-style=italic}) is the ||brain||{color=blue} of the computer.

### User Interface

Click ||Save||{background=green color=white padding=4px 12px border-radius=4px} to save your changes.

||Cancel||{background=gray color=white padding=4px 12px border-radius=4px} to go back.

### Status Indicators

- Status: ||Online||{color=green font-weight=bold}
- Status: ||Offline||{color=gray}
- Status: ||Error||{color=red font-weight=bold}

### Warnings and Tips

||Warning: This action cannot be undone!||{color=red font-weight=bold background=#FEE2E2 padding=4px 8px}

||Tip: Use keyboard shortcuts to save time!||{color=#065F46 background=#D1FAE5 padding=4px 8px}

### Emphasis in Sentences

The key to ||success||{color=green font-weight=bold} is ||consistency||{color=blue} and ||perseverance||{color=purple}.

## Nested Inline Styling

You can nest inline styling:

This is ||bold and colored||{color=blue} ||within more styled text||{color=red font-weight=bold}

## Complex Examples

### Product Feature

||Feature:||{font-weight=bold color=blue} ||Dark Mode||{color=purple font-weight=background=#F3E8FF padding=2px 6px}

||Supports automatic theme switching||{color=gray font-size=0.9em}

### Version Information

- ||Version:||{font-weight=bold} ||2.0.0||{background=green color=white padding=2px 6px border-radius=4px font-family=monospace}
- ||Released:||{font-weight=bold} ||2026-02-18||{color=gray}

### Code Snippet with Syntax

The ||Array.map()||{font-family=monospace background=#1F2937 color=#60A5FA padding=2px 6px} method creates a new array by calling a function on every element.

### Price Display

- Regular price: ||$99.99||{color=gray text-decoration=line-through}
- Sale price: ||$49.99||{color=red font-weight=bold font-size=1.2em}

### Progress Indicators

Progress: ||75%||{background=#10B981 color=white padding=2px 8px border-radius=4px font-weight=bold}

### Accessibility Labels

Visually hidden but accessible (screen reader only) : "||Visually hidden text||{visually-hidden=true}"

Note: `sr-only=true` is an alias for `visually-hidden=true` for compatibility with other frameworks.

## Creative Uses

### Highlighting Key Terms

In ||computer science||{font-weight=bold color=blue}, a ||variable||{font-family=monospace background=#F3F4F6} is a storage location with an associated name.

### Emotional Text

- This is ||exciting!||{color=green font-size=1.1em}
- This is ||dangerous||{color=red font-weight=bold}
- This is ||mysterious||{color=purple font-style=italic}

### Flow and Emphasis

The ||main||{font-weight=bold} reason for using Zolt is its ||simplicity||{color=blue} and ||power||{color=purple}.

### Text Watermarks

- ||DRAFT||{color=gray font-size=3em opacity=0.3 transform=rotate(-45deg)}
- ||CONFIDENTIAL||{color=red font-size=2em opacity=0.5}

